import java.util.* ;
import java.io.*; 
public class Solution {
	public static StringBuilder replaceSpaces(StringBuilder str) {
		// Write your code here.

		int n = str.length();

		for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
			char ch = str.charAt(i);

			if(ch == ' '){
				str.replace(i,i+1,"@40");
				n += 2;
			}
		}
		return str;
	}
}

You have been given a string 'STR' of words. You need to replace all the spaces between words with “@40”.

Sample Input 1:
Coding Ninjas Is A Coding Platform
Hello World

Sample Output 1:
Coding@40Ninjas@40Is@40A@40Coding@40Platform
Hello@40World
Explanation of Sample Output 1:
In test case 1, After replacing the spaces with “@40” string is: 
Coding@40Ninjas@40Is@40A@40Coding@40Platform



T.C => O(N)
S.C => O(1)
